# Flash-Cards — Cursor AI Rules

## Onboarding Protocol

When a new agent starts, they must follow the five-step onboarding protocol:

1. **Read `!!! START HERE - READ FIRST.md`** (root directory)
2. **Read `docs/AGENT_ONBOARDING_PROTOCOL.md`** for complete onboarding
3. **Check `docs/AGENT_STATUS.md`** for current project status
4. **Review `docs/Standards.md`** for coding and design standards
5. **Run `pnpm install && pnpm dev`** to get the app running

## Agent Handoff

At the end of each session, run:
```bash
pnpm run handoff:generate
```

This updates `docs/AGENT_STATUS.md` with current context for the next agent.

## Project Context

- **Dual Deployment**: Next.js app (`pages/`, `components/`) + single-file GitHub Pages (`index.html`, `app.js`)
- **Brand**: Scottsdale Cart Tours — use `BRAND` tokens from `config/brand.ts`
- **Design**: Minimalist, luxury-brand aesthetic; no emojis; accessible; responsive
- **Audio**: Pre-generated MP3s in `audio/` with SpeechSynthesis fallback
- **Data Sync**: After changing `lib/data.ts`, run `node scripts/sync-decks.js`

## Code Standards

- TypeScript-first: no `any`, explicit function signatures
- Components: PascalCase in `components/`
- Styling: Tailwind utility classes, use `BRAND` tokens
- Accessibility: Semantic HTML, ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation
- Imports: ES modules with `@/` aliases
- Error handling: Graceful fallbacks, user-friendly states

## Testing

- Unit tests: `pnpm test` (Jest)
- E2E tests: `pnpm test:e2e` (Playwright)
- All tests: `pnpm test:all`
- Code quality: `pnpm lint`, `pnpm type-check`

## Important Reminders

- Always check both Next.js and single-file versions when making changes
- Keep `index.html` and `app.js` in sync with React components
- Use `BRAND` constants for all colors, typography, radii, shadows
- Mobile-first: All UI must be responsive and touch-optimized
- Run `pnpm run handoff:generate` before ending your session

